---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';

const sections = (await getCollection('framework')).sort(
	(a, b) => a.data.order - b.data.order,
);
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`The Christian Resilience Framework — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="Navigating 2026–2030: A framework for faith, family, and resilience in the age of artificial intelligence."
		/>
		<style>
			main {
				max-width: 720px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 3rem 1rem 5rem;
			}
			.page-label {
				font-family: "Lora", Georgia, serif;
				font-size: 0.72rem;
				font-weight: 600;
				letter-spacing: 0.18em;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
			}
			.listing-rule {
				height: 2px;
				background: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
				margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
			}
			h1 {
				font-size: 2.4rem;
				margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
				line-height: 1.15;
			}
			.subtitle {
				font-family: "Lora", Georgia, serif;
				font-style: italic;
				font-size: 0.97rem;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				margin-top: 0;
				margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
			}
			.preamble {
				border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
				padding: 0.5em 0 0.5em 1.5em;
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
				font-style: italic;
				font-size: 1rem;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
				line-height: 1.85;
				background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.2);
				border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
			}
			.preamble p { margin-bottom: 1em; }
			.preamble p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
			.section-list {
				list-style: none;
				margin: 0;
				padding: 0;
			}
			.section-item {
				border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
			}
			.section-item a {
				display: flex;
				align-items: flex-start;
				gap: 1.5rem;
				padding: 1.5rem 0.25rem;
				text-decoration: none;
				transition: background 0.15s;
			}
			.section-item a:hover .section-title {
				color: var(--accent);
			}
			.section-num {
				font-family: "Playfair Display", Georgia, serif;
				font-size: 1.5rem;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-light));
				min-width: 2.75rem;
				line-height: 1.2;
				padding-top: 0.05rem;
				user-select: none;
				flex-shrink: 0;
			}
			.section-body {
				flex: 1;
				min-width: 0;
			}
			.section-title {
				font-family: "Playfair Display", Georgia, serif;
				font-size: 1.2rem;
				font-weight: 700;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
				margin: 0 0 0.3rem 0;
				line-height: 1.3;
				transition: color 0.15s;
			}
			.section-desc {
				font-family: "Lora", Georgia, serif;
				font-size: 0.88rem;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				margin: 0;
				line-height: 1.55;
			}
			.section-arrow {
				color: var(--accent);
				font-size: 1rem;
				opacity: 0;
				transition: opacity 0.15s;
				padding-top: 0.15rem;
				flex-shrink: 0;
			}
			.section-item a:hover .section-arrow {
				opacity: 1;
			}
			@media (max-width: 640px) {
				.section-num { display: none; }
				.section-arrow { opacity: 1; }
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<p class="page-label">The Christian Resilience Framework</p>
			<div class="listing-rule"></div>
			<h1>Navigating 2026–2030</h1>
			<p class="subtitle">Faith, family, and resilience in the age of artificial intelligence.</p>

			<div class="preamble">
				<p>Glory be to God, the Alpha and the Omega, who remains sovereign over every age and every invention of man. We recognize that technology is not inherently evil. Rather, technology is an integral part of humanity. From the first spark of fire to the mastery of farming, tools and technology have served as profound instruments for the common good and a participation in God's creative work.</p>
				<p>Yet, while Christians have navigated the challenges of new technologies for centuries, the current shift toward a post-human landscape is different in kind, presenting an unprecedented challenge to the very definition of being made in the Image of God. AI will allow us to do things that were unthinkable 10 years ago: cure cancer, solve housing shortages, feed the poor. The possibilities are endless! Yet…we must also ask difficult questions. What is the cost of these new godlike powers?</p>
				<p>To meet this moment, we must engage in a radical re-evaluation of how we live, work, and pray, ensuring our primary allegiance remains to the Creator rather than to the machine. <strong>This is real. God is bigger. Let's go.</strong></p>
			</div>

			<ol class="section-list">
				{sections.map((section) => (
					<li class="section-item">
						<a href={`/framework/${section.id}/`}>
							<div class="section-num">{String(section.data.order).padStart(2, '0')}</div>
							<div class="section-body">
								<h2 class="section-title">{section.data.title}</h2>
								{section.data.description && (
									<p class="section-desc">{section.data.description}</p>
								)}
							</div>
							<div class="section-arrow">→</div>
						</a>
					</li>
				))}
			</ol>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
